               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Taʾāmra Māryām "Miracles of Mary" (fols. 3ra-112rb)&#xD; I-1) Maṣḥafa
                     śǝrʿāt, Introductory rite of al-Muʿallaqah and hymn (fols. 3ra-6va)&#xD; I-2)
                     Introductory exhortation and hymns (fols. 6va-9rb)&#xD; I-3) ʾƎsaggǝd laki
                     wa-ʾǝweddǝsaki... "I worship Thee..." (fol. 9rb-10rb)&#xD; I-4) Taʾāmra Māryām
                     "Miracles of Mary": 65 miracles (fols. 10ra-112rb)</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text I-1 contains the hymns: salām laki ḫoḫǝta mǝśrāq ... "Salutation to
                        you, Threshold of the East ..." (<locus target="#6ra">6ra</locus>)
                        <!-- = LIT4714Salamlaki (MV 2017-09-07) -->.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text I-2 includes the hymns:</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl ba-kǝlʾe Māryām ... "O my Lady, Holy
                        Two-fold Virgin Mary ..." (<locus target="#8ra">8ra</locus> l.16-8rb)</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl Māryām ʾǝmmu la-ʾIyasus Krǝstos kahāli ...
                        "O my Lady, Holy Virgin Mary, Mother of Jesus Christ the Almighty ..."
                           (<locus target="#8rb">8rb-</locus>va) (cp. ChRep n<locus target="#373">373</locus>)</note>
                     <note>- salām laki ʾo-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl Māryām ʾǝmma madḫǝn wa-ʾǝmma
                        bǝrhān ... "Salutation to you, o my Lady, Holy Virgin Mary, Mother of the
                        Saviour and Mother of the Light ..." (<locus from="8va" to="9rb">8va-9rb</locus>).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>The miracles of St Mary (Text I-4) are not numbered.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Some fols. have a single ruled line at the top and at the bottom, very
                        close to the edge of the folio (e.g., <locus target="#12rv">12rv</locus>,
                        17rv), possibly used as orientation for cutting parchment leaves.</note>
                  </msItem>
